# LucidGate example list: bannedregexpheaderlist
# Format: One Go regular expression per line matched against flattened "Header: value" lines.
# Lines beginning with # are comments and are ignored by the loader.
# To activate a rule, copy one example, remove the leading # and adapt it to your environment.
# You can include another file with: .Include<relative-or-absolute-path>
#
# Commented examples:
# (?i)^X-Tracker:.*enabled
# (?i)^X-Risk-Score:\s*high
# (?i)^X-Debug-Mode:\s*true
# (?i)^User-Agent:.*blocked-client
# (?i)^Referer:\s*http://untrusted\.example
# (?i)^Authorization:\s*Bearer\s+[A-Za-z0-9._-]+
# (?i)^X-Forwarded-For:\s*10\.
# (?i)^X-Leak-Marker:.*secret
# (?i)^Cookie:.*tracking_id=
# (?i)^X-Experiment:\s*unsafe
